        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Add per-DM active directive prompt",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a DM-scoped active directive path so deployments can steer direct-message behavior for a turn without folding that directive into ambient group/subagent context.\n\nThe new `agents.defaults.dmDirective` setting is routed as `extraSystemPromptDirective` through the reply runner, CLI runner, and embedded runner paths. The system-prompt assembler renders it as the final system block after `## Runtime`:\n\n```text\n## Active Directive (overrides persona for this turn)\n```\n\nAmbient `extraSystemPrompt` behavior is unchanged, so existing group `GroupSystemPrompt` content still renders under `## Group Chat Context`.\n\n## Why\n\nOpenClaw currently sends all per-turn extra prompt material through the same ambient context slot. That makes a direct-message override such as “for this context behave like X” compete poorly with durable persona/project context such as `SOUL.md`.\n\nThis keeps the existing context path intact and introduces one explicit directive path for DM-only steering.\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Adds `agents.defaults.dmDirective` config/schema support.\n- Routes `dmDirective` only for direct chats.\n- Keeps the directive separate from `extraSystemPrompt` and followup prompt fusion.\n- Forwards the field through both CLI and embedded execution paths.\n- Renders the directive after Runtime as the last system block before the user message.\n- Adds focused tests for prompt ordering and DM-only routing.\n\n## Validation\n\n```bash\nnode node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts\n```\n\nResult: 2 test files passed, 163 tests passed.\n\nAlso ran:\n\n```bash\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nResult: clean.\n",
